roton) \n| [[Calabria]] \n| {{Hs|Ita}}[[Magna Graecia]], Italy \n| data-sort-value=\"-710\" | 710 BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n| Greek colony.\n|-\n| [[Taranto]] (as Taras) \n| [[Magna Graecia]] \n| {{Hs|Ita}}[[Apulia]], Italy \n| data-sort-value=\"-706\" | 706 BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}} \n| Founded as the only Spartan colony by the Partheniae, children of unmarried Spartan women and '' perioikoi'', free non-citizen residents of Sparta and her territories.\n|-\n| [[Corfu (city)|Corfu]], ''Kerkyra'' \n| [[Corfu]] \n| {{Hs|Gre}}[[Ionian Islands]], Greece \n| data-sort-value=\"-700\" | 700 BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}} \n| A colony of the Greek city of Corinth.\n|-\n| [[Kerch]] (as [[Panticapaeum]]) \n| [[Greeks in pre-Roman Crimea|pre-Roman Crimea]] \n| [[Crimea]], [[Ukraine]]\n| data-sort-value=\"-700\" | 7th century BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}} \n| Greek colony.\n|-\n| [[Feodosiya]] (as Theodosia) \n| [[Greeks in pre-Roman Crimea|pre-Roman Crimea]] \n| [[Crimea]], [[Ukraine]]\n| data-sort-value=\"-700\" | 7th century BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n| Greek colony.\n|-\n| [[Istanbul]] (as [[Byzantion]])\n| [[Thrace]], [[Anatolia]]\n| [[Turkey]]\n| data-sort-value=\"-685\" | 685 BC Anatolia; 660 BC Thrace<ref name=autogenerated1 />\n|Founded as a colony of [[Megara]]; Neolithic site dated to 6400 BC, over port of Lygos by Thracians c. 1150 BC.\n|-\n| [[Naples]]\n| [[Magna Graecia]]\n| Italy\n| data-sort-value=\"-680\" | c. 680 BC<ref name=\"greeknaples\">{{cite news|url=http://faculty.ed.umuc.edu/~jmatthew/naples/Greek_Naples.html |publisher=Faculty.ed.umuc.edu |title=Greek Naples |date=8 January 2008 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110611095615/http://faculty.ed.umuc.edu/~jmatthew/naples/Greek_Naples.html |archivedate=June 11, 2011}}</ref>\n|Actually the date at which an older settlement close by, called ''Parthenope'', was founded by settlers from [[Cumae]]. This eventually merged with Neapolis prope