is.\n|-\n| [[Mangalia]] \n| [[Dacia]] \n| [[Romania]] \n| data-sort-value=\"-600\" | 6th century BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}|| Founded as ''Callatis''.\n|-\n| [[Constan\u0163a]] \n| [[Dacia]] \n| [[Romania]] \n| data-sort-value=\"-600\" | 6th century BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}} \n| Founded as ''Tomis''.\n|-\n| [[Mantua]] \n| [[Po Valley]]\n| {{Hs|Ita}}[[Lombardy]], Italy \n| data-sort-value=\"-600\" | 6th century BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n| Village settlement since c. 2000 BC; became an [[Etruscan civilisation|Etruscan]] city in the 6th century BC.\n|-\n| [[Milan]] \n| [[Po Valley]], [[Cisalpine Gaul]]\n| {{Hs|Ita}}[[Lombardy]], [[Italy]]\n| data-sort-value=\"-600\" | 6th century BC\n| Founded by the [[Insubres]] in the 6th century BC according to [[Titus Livy]]. Conquered by the Romans in 222 BC.\n|-\n| [[Bilhorod-Dnistrovskyi]] (as [[Tyras]]) \n| [[Bessarabia]] \n| [[Ukraine]] \n| data-sort-value=\"-600\" | 6th century BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Kutaisi]]\n| [[Colchis]]\n| [[Imereti]] province, [[Georgia (country)|Georgia]]\n| data-sort-value=\"-600\" | 6th to 4th century BC \n|Archaeological evidence indicates that the city functioned as the capital of the kingdom of [[Colchis]] in the sixth to fifth centuries BC.<ref>Gela Gamkrelidze. ''RESEARCHES IN IBERIA-COLCHOLOGY''. Edited by David Braiind (Prof, of University of Exeter (UK)) // Olar LORDKIPANIDZE CENTRE OF ARCHAEOLOGY OF GEORGIAN NATIONAL MUSEUM. P. 43 \"According to the data on archaeological excavations on the Gabashvili, Dateshidze and Ukimerioni hills in Kutaisi, an urban-type settlement of the 6-5 cent. BC was found to be concentrated\"</ref>\n|-\n| [[Varna]] \n| [[Thrace]] \n| {{Hs|Bul}}[[Bulgarian Black Sea Coast]], [[Bulgaria]] \n| data-sort-value=\"-585\" | 585\u2013570 BC{{citation needed|date=June 2016}} \n| Founded<ref>An Inventory of Archaic and Classical Poleis: An Investigation Conducted by The Copenhagen Polis Centre for the Danish Nationa