anshi|Yanshi, Henan]] ([[Erlitou Site]]) \n| [[Xia dynasty]] ([[Erlitou culture]]) \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Henan]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-1900\" | c. 1900 BC {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Luoyang]] (as ''Xibo, Luoyi, Zhongguo, Henan, Dongdu, Shendu'') \n| [[Shang dynasty|Shang Dynasty]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Henan]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-1600\" | c. 1600 BC {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Xi'an]] (as ''Haojing, Fenghao, Chang'an, Jingzhao,  Daxing'') \n| [[Zhou dynasty|Zhou Dynasty]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Shaanxi]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-1100\" | c. 1100 BC {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Handan]] \n| [[Jin (Chinese state)|Jin]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Hebei]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-1080\" | c. 1080 BC {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|\n|-\n| [[History of Beijing|Beijing]] (as ''Ji, Youzhou, Fanyang, Yanjing, Zhongdu, Dadu) \n| [[Ji (state)|Ji]], [[Yan (state)|Yan]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Beijing]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-1045\" | c. 1045 BC \n| [[List of Paleolithic sites in China|Paleolithic]] ''[[homo sapiens]]'' lived in the caves from about 27,000 to 10,000 years ago.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.unesco.org/ext/field/beijing/whc/pkm-site.htm|title=Beijing|website=UNESCO|date=2019-05-17}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[Zibo]] (as ''Yingqiu, Linzi, Qiling, Zichuan, Boping'') \n| [[Qi (state)|Qi]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Shandong]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-1045\" | c. 1045 BC {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n| The Lord of Qi, Jiang Ziya, set the capital of his manor at Yingqiu(\u8425\u4e18), which is today's Linzi District.\n|-\n| [[Jingzhou]] (as ''Jinan, Yingdu,  Jiangling, Jingsha, Nanjun'') \n| [[Chu (state)|Chu]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}} [[Hubei]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-689\" | c. 689 BC {{citation needed|date=February 2020}}\n|\n|-\n| [[Hefei]] (as ''Luyi, Ruyin, Luzhou, Hezhou, Lujiang'') \n| [[Zhou dynasty|Zhou Dynasty]] \n| {{Hs|Chi}}[[Anhui]], China \n| data-sort-value=\"-650\" | c. 650 BC \n| Th